-- Anti-Military Group Claims Responsibility for Quebec Bombing: La Presse
-- Kevin Bell
-- 2010-07-02T17:43:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/anti-military-group-claims-responsibility-for-quebec-bombing-la-presse.html

          
          
             An anti-military group claimed
responsibility for an explosion that damaged a Canadian Forces
recruiting office in Quebec early today, La Presse newspaper
reported.  
 The group, International Resistance, said it opposes the
militaristic ideals and practices of the Canadian state,  La
Presse said , citing a statement sent to the newspaper.  
 Nobody was injured in the blast, which occurred about 3
a.m. New York time at a military recruiting office in downtown
Trois-Rivieres, about 140 kilometers (87 miles) northeast of
Montreal, the newspaper said.  
